{"questionId":"27271","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Two capacitors C<sub>1</sub> and C<sub>2</sub> of capacitance 28 µF and 22 µF respectively are connected in&nbsp;a circuit with a two-way switch and a cell of emf 1.5 V with a negligible internal resistance.&nbsp;The capacitors are initially uncharged. The switch is then connected to position A.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/8c000573f10c398e7a970a2f63888732450f755d.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A cell is now connected by a switch to a coil X. A second coil Y of cross-sectional area&nbsp;6.4 cm<sup>2</sup> with 5 turns is looped around coil X and connected to an ideal voltmeter.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/4812f5d4be2c6f9b05159b375a5bf3792bb86623.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The graph shows the variation with <em>t</em> of the magnetic flux density <em>B</em> in coil Y.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/d06b46453926f52b243587545a7340d7b2ff9969.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine the average emf induced across coil Y in the first 3.0 ms.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempted use of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ε</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>∆</mo><mi>Φ</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>∆</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;<em><strong>OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>N</mi><mi>A</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>∆</mo><mi>B</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>∆</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;✓</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ε</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>×</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow>